This is the draft master-copy of Brute Beauty And Valour And Act, Oh, Air, Pride, Plume, Here Buckle!

books
└── brute
    ├── index.html        Not part of the book, just here as a place to browsing the draft
    ├── cover.png         Place-holder bookcover.
    ├── bookinfo.json     Metadata for EPUB and LaTeX front matter
    ├── Text
    │   ├── toc.xhtml      Table of contents. This gives the chapter order.
    │   ├── preface.xhtml
    │   ├── title.xhtml
    │   ├── copyright.xhtml
    │   ├── nnnnn_the_chapters_title.xhtml   nnnn = the Wordpress post number
    │   └── ...
    ├── Text
    ├── Images            Images used in the Text pages. All GIFs have been converted to PNG.
    └── Styles
        └── style.css     A placeholder style. Emulates the look of the PDF version.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
XHTML 

The XHTML used is a subset that is covers everything used in the blog, is acceptable in an 
EPUB and is enough to generate LaTeX from. These can be added to where necessary.

Span level tags:

    strong sup tt     
    br 
    a
    del                  struck-out text

Block level tags:

    h1                 for post headings
    h2                 un-indexed subheadings
    ol
    ul
    p
    p.noindent         Unidented paragraph. Occurs after headings, illustations and block quotes.
    p.center           Centered text
    
    p.textbreak        Contains the asterisks placed between paragraphs.
    
    blockquote         For quotations, 
         p                which always contain at least one paragraph

    p.verse            a stanza of verse,
    p.linebreaks       or any other paragraph with linebreaks
         br

    div.blockparagraphs   text which look best as unindented paragraphs separated by vertical whitespace
         p
         
    div.illustration   One or more illustration images, to be placed in a row.
         p.imagerow
            img
         p.caption


